Make configure.ac work with autoconf 2.73

autoreconf requires "AC_INIT" to appear in configure.ac. Prior to autoconf 2.73,
our indirect invocation via K5_AC_INIT() was sufficient, but now the regular
expression match checks for word boundaries. Get rid of K5_AC_INIT(), moving the
version extraction code from aclocal.m4 to a new file version.m4. In the moved
versioning code, use m4_fatal() to simplify error handling.

Fixes:

autoreconf: error: configure.ac: AC_INIT not found; not an autoconf script?

https://krbdev.mit.edu/rt/Ticket/Display.html?id=9202
https://github.com/krb5/krb5/commit/b7290e0cab5b7e39cd4aa7c098beb18a886d4a1d
--- aclocal.m4
+++ aclocal.m4
@@ -16,30 +16,6 @@ ac_config_fragdir=$ac_reltopdir/config
 AC_CONFIG_AUX_DIR(K5_TOPDIR/config)
 ])dnl
